<p>The <code>get</code> tag retrieves content from the content store or includes files.</p>

<h2>Store and Get Content</h2>
<pre>{open}content 'greeting'{close}Hello, World!{open}/content{close}
{open}get 'greeting'{close}</pre>
{content 'greeting'}Hello, World!{/content}
<p>Result: {get 'greeting'}</p>

<h2>Store HTML and Retrieve</h2>
<pre>{open}content 'button'{close}&lt;button&gt;Click Me&lt;/button&gt;{open}/content{close}
{open}get 'button'{close}</pre>
{content 'button'}<button>Click Me</button>{/content}
<p>Result: {get 'button'}</p>

<h2>Reuse Stored Content Multiple Times</h2>
<pre>{open}content 'star'{close}*{open}/content{close}
{open}get 'star'{close}{open}get 'star'{close}{open}get 'star'{close}{open}get 'star'{close}{open}get 'star'{close}</pre>
{content 'star'}*{/content}
<p>Result: {get 'star'}{get 'star'}{get 'star'}{get 'star'}{get 'star'}</p>

<h2>Dynamic Content Storage</h2>
<pre>{open}set user='Alice'{close}
{open}content 'welcome'{close}Welcome back, {open}$user{close}!{open}/content{close}
{open}get 'welcome'{close}</pre>
{set user='Alice'}
{content 'welcome'}Welcome back, {$user}!{/content}
<p>Result: {get 'welcome'}</p>

<h2>Store Template Fragment</h2>
<pre>{open}content 'listItem'{close}&lt;li style="color:blue"&gt;Item&lt;/li&gt;{open}/content{close}
&lt;ul&gt;
  {open}get 'listItem'{close}
  {open}get 'listItem'{close}
  {open}get 'listItem'{close}
&lt;/ul&gt;</pre>
{content 'listItem'}<li style="color:blue">Item</li>{/content}
<ul>
  {get 'listItem'}
  {get 'listItem'}
  {get 'listItem'}
</ul>
